              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Copy -->
        <div class="fig-cell fig-cell--border-top">
          <h2 class="type-xl weight-bold">if you're good at chess, you play 5 games at once</h2>
          <p class="type-sm" style="opacity: 0.8; margin-bottom: var(--space-sm)">most coding agents sit idle while tests run, apis respond, and tool calls return. twig doesn't wait.</p>
          <p class="type-sm" style="opacity: 0.8">it spins up one agent per signal, each in its own git worktree — all moving in parallel, none aware of each other, no merge conflicts when they're done.</p>
